President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. Jerry L. Johnson, currently a principal partner for Heffler, Radetick & Saitta, LLP, will be appointed as a member of the Advisory Group on Prevention, Health Promotion, and Integrative and Public Health. Dr. Jacob Lozada, currently serving on various boards and committees, will also be appointed as a member of the Advisory Group. Dr. Dean Ornish, founder and president of the Preventive Medicine Research Institute, will join the Advisory Group as well. Dr. Herminia Palacio, Executive Director of Harris County Public Health and Environmental Services, will be appointed as a member of the Advisory Group. Lastly, Kent A. Salazar, owner of Kent Salazar Co., will be appointed as a member of the Board of Directors of the Valles Caldera Trust.